SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 174
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Bennett McLain of
North Greene High School, 2025 U.S.
Presidential Scholars Program nominee.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pay tribute to
those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to excellence,
have distinguished themselves in the classroom and beyond; and
WHEREAS, Bennett McLain of North Greene High School is one such exceptional
student, who was recently named as a nominee in the General Academics component of the
2025 U.S. Presidential Scholars Program; and
WHEREAS, established in 1964 by executive order of the president, the U.S.
Presidential Scholars Program recognizes some of the nation's most distinguished graduating
high school seniors for their accomplishments in academics, leadership, community service, the
arts, and career and technical fields; and
WHEREAS, inclusion in the U.S. Presidential Scholars Program is an elite honor, with
only 5,000 candidates selected from a pool of approximately 3.6 million students from
throughout the country; and
WHEREAS, Mr. McLain distinguished himself from his peers with his general academic
excellence, community involvement, remarkable leadership, and superlative writing talent, skills
he will surely put to fine use in his future endeavors; and
WHEREAS, the son of David and Delana McLain, Bennett has proven himself to be a
student of the highest caliber not only in Tennessee but also in the nation; this distinct honor
most certainly bodes well for his future success; and
